"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code incorrectly uses the `sns.set_style()` function with the `rc` argument. According to the seaborn documentation, the `rc` argument can only be used to override parameters that are part of the style definition. The parameters 'axes.grid' and 'grid.color' are not part of the style definition and should not be passed in this way. Instead, they should be set using the `set_style()` function without the `rc` argument.\",\n  \"patch\": \"14c14\\n< sns.set_style(rc=style_dict)\\n---\\n> sns.set_style('whitegrid')\\n> plt.rcParams.update(style_dict)\"\n}"